{
  "texts": [
    "This investigation demonstrates that a wide range of parameters affect image segmentation-based technology.",
    "The dents and alterations causing diseases of the plants may be identified using this method in contrast to diseases that result in damages that cannot be seen from the photos of the plants (Loey et al. 2020).",
    "This investigation also reveals a deficient database that might be utilized to offer context for contrasting the captured photos (Barbedo 2018b).",
    "The segmentation of large-scale images under complex and real-world natural scenes will continue to be a focus and a challenging area of research because various natural environment factors, such as wind velocity, illumination, temperature, humidity, and background, influence the acquisition and obtaining images of disease.",
    "Another difficulty is that different diseases might have various symptoms and features that are quite similar (Barbedo 2018a)."
  ]
}